setupVTable

private void setupVTable()
Go through all the parents and get their virtual methods, then just add them. To do this, we test if we first have a parent (java.lang.Object doesn't); if we have a parent, grab his virtual methods, see if we override them (they'll be set in either this.pMethods or this.vMethods), if we don't, then add them, otherwise, ignore. Since we know that there are problems with VTable resolution from parents, we're going to first add our methods to our vtable and grab our parents, then we're going to activate our methods so that they translate.

visitExtension

public void visitExtension(xtc.tree.GNode n)
Handles resolving dependencies for inheritance. When it sees an extension, it throws the name to its parent file's import manager in order to resolve the name and activate the class so that it can extend it properly.
